RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 79. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $6,600 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $20,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WAGON TRAIN lead the way into the turn under a steady drive then drew off in the stretch to prevail in the end wire to wire. MIAMI MOONLIGHT tracked the pace from the inside down the backstretch, then bid on the turn to dig in gamely in the early stretch, drifted out then continued to close belatedly but it wasn't enough in the end. FRIDAYNIGHTSOLDIER tracked the pace while two then came out four wide on the turn to rally in the stretch and was closing well but it was too late. WITHOUT A SONG stalked the pace from the inside, then came out three wide to rally on the turn and into the stretch but it wasn't enough. BOMBER COMMAND was in a strong drive to press the pace into the turn while two wide, rallied in the early stretch but had nothing left and weakened in the end. MILLCREEK ROAD broke outwardly at the start, then raced behind the field along the inside throughout and was no factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 1 1/16M Turf CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $6,600 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $20,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts). (If Deemed inadvisable by manageme nt to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Sixteenth.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEAR BEAU (IRE) reserved well off the early pace near the rear of the field, commenced a rally in the far turn circling the pack was set down for the drive on the outside and closed willingly to be up in the final strides. OIL N CANDY tracked the leaders from the pocket while racing along the rail, lost some position in the turn when the pack tightened, cut the corner turning for home and closed willingly up the fence to just miss MYLITTLEWISKEYGIRL stalked the loose frontrunners down the backstretch from two wide, made a three wide bid in the turn to take the lead in mid-stretch but failed to hold off the two closers in a good effort. GLORY O broke outward into rival, raced up from four wide into the first turn to take the lead, settled into a duel on the front end finally taking command in upper stretch and weakened late in the drive. CHARMING LEAH well position following the leaders down the backside from between horses two wide, loomed up turning from home from three wide, briefly took the lead and was out-finished down the lane. OCCURRENCE trailed the field to the far turn and showed mild interest late making gains down the stretch. TIZ A KNOCKOUT squeezed at the start to drop back, gathered up to settle into stride and went evenly never posing a threat. WISE MEMORIES flashed early speed to duel on the lead for the first three-quarters of a mile and tired from there.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TEXAS ASCOT QUEEN dueled from the two path throughout the first three quarters then dug in gamely in the early stretch to kick clear and was ridden out to the end. IMA SKY TRAVELER dueled with an outer rival down the backstretch and into the early stretch, then continued to menace grudgingly but was outkicked in the end. PROUD VALENTINE chased the pace from the two path, was moving up while four wide on the turn, then bid in the stretch but came up empty. MRS. RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 4 1M Turf CR: 67. Allowance Purse 33500. (PLUS UP TO $1,675 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-wi nners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 18, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUN WITT RUN reared at the start giving the field a length, moved into a comfortable tracking position along the rail, made a steady gain down the backside to be in contention in the pocket turning for home, accelerated quickly to burst to the lead and be going away late after patient handling. MISSINGYOUCRAZY sped off to take control down the lane the first time, maintained a well rated clear lead into the far turn, responded when challenged turning for home and held the lead until mid-stretch when he ducked out several paths, was straightened away and finished up second best. XTRA SPICY stalked the pace in striking distance through out, moved up late in the far turn to loom boldly and finished evenly down the lane. WICKED SONG tracked the pace from two wide down the backstretch, veered out off heels down the backside briefly impeding rival, continued to be prominent from four wide and flattened out late in the drive. GOVERNOR ANN settled near the rear of the field to the far turn and made a mild bid in the stretch to close some ground. TEXAS TWINKIES raced three wide down the backside, was brushed down the backside when rival moved off heels, and went evenly from there never a threat. KAUSE I'M DEVINE was rank for the first half mile and proved to be no factor. TRANQUILITY flashed brief early foot and steadily faded to the rear.

PUNTO RAFFA VOLO stalked the pace early from the inside, then slowly faded and wsa through early.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 6 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 98. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 18000. (PLUS UP TO $3,600 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000 OR LESS SINCE MAY 18, 2021 OR CLAIMING PRICE $15,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 18 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Races Where Entered For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOOD SCOUT hustled hard away from the gate to take the lead, came under a drive at the quarter pole, surrendered the lead in upper stretch and battled back under strong handling to gain the advantage. IMA BLING CAT broke alertly, pressed the pace from two wide through the turn, took command turning for home and was out-finished late in the lane. COLTONS DREAM chased the leaders from the gate to the wire in striking position but failed to gain on the top two. SWEET RIVER BAINES settled off the rapid early pace along the fence, angled out for the drive and finished with a late mild bid. POMEROY HAZE slow early to be near the rear of the field and passed tiring rivals through the stretch. SIDETOWN broke near the back of the pack, rushed up into mid-pack contention and faded through the lane. SHE'S AN ANGEL tossed head at the start, moved up briefly and finished up as no threat having lost most of his chance at the start. REACH THE CIRCLE was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 7 7 1/2F Turf CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. (PLUS UP TO $3,400 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $30,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the t urf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile. If the race is for two year olds, it will be run at Seven Furlongs.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BASKET CASE lead the way into the first turn, was headed by an outside rival in the early backstretch, then regained the lead heading into the far turn, then drew off in the stretch to prove best in the end. JAZZY LASSIE chased the pace from the inside then bid on the far turn, then closed well while splitting rivals to be up for the place position. GOLD MAKIN GIRL was out four wide while heading into the first turn, was gaining ground gamely throughout to rally in the home stretch while five wide and closed strong in the end. VA VOOM chased the pace while two wide, was in a hard drive on the turn to close well in the stretch just missing the show prize. MUCHO MAMA MIA veered out at the start and bumped rival, then raced along the inside down the backstretch, was urging on the far turn, came out five wide to rally in the stretch but it wasn't enough. BOBBIE O raced in the middle of the field while two wide, then bid on the far turn but came up evenly in the stretch. HOT COOKIE broke inwardly at the start, the settled along the inside at an even pace throughout, rallied in the stretch and was no threat. BERING'S SPECIAL was forwardly placed while three wide,was in a hard drive to vie for the lead in the early backstretch, was used up then slowly faded throughout the second half of the course. TRICKY CARLA was squeezed back at the start and had no chance. POWER TO PLAY broke outwardly at the start, then was moving down the backstretch swiftly from the three path to gain the short lead, then was overtaken heading into the far turn and lost momentum in the final furlongs.

ENTRY.OWNER: Mazoch Linda Mazoch Michael J and Gustafson Austin
ENTRY.COMMENT: lead 1st, headed backstretch, regain lead, held well,driving
